# Improvement task discovery (requestable)

When **researching** friction to **log** as improvement work (**`type: "improvement"`** tasks and/or **`generate-recommendations`** / transcript ingest):

1. Follow **`.ai/playbooks/improvement-task-discovery.md`** (playbook id `improvement-task-discovery`). Attach it (`@`) so the checklist stays in view.
2. **Synthesize a problem report** before persisting: use **`metadata.issue`** + **`metadata.supportingReasoning`** (and task **`approach`** / scope / acceptance)—do **not** dump raw transcripts or tool traces as the improvement body.
3. Use **`.ai/AGENT-CLI-MAP.md`** for Tier **B** improvement commands; JSON **`policyApproval`** in the **third** CLI argument per **`.ai/POLICY-APPROVAL.md`**.
4. Prefer **`workspace-kit`** for persistence over chat-only summaries; run **`ingest-transcripts`** / **`generate-recommendations`** on a regular cadence when transcripts or friction signals exist (see playbook §6).

Invocation: **`.ai/runbooks/agent-playbooks.md`**.

This rule does **not** override **`workspace-kit-cli-execution.mdc`** or **`maintainer-delivery-loop.mdc`**.
